  "body": "I am using LightGBM for a ranking task. My dataset has no missing values, but I note that for some features, the Expected SHAP value is negative or positive.\r\n\r\nFor ranking tasks, the ranking of a set of documents in a query is determined based on sorting the output values of a model. So model output values are on an arbitrary scale and are interpreted relative to other documents.\r\n\r\nIf a feature has a negative expected SHAP value, does it make sense to center the SHAP values for that feature before calculating Mean |SHAP| value? If so, should I center by Query or at the Corpus level?\r\n\r\nMy reasoning is that if a feature contributes a similar negative amount to all documents, then it may be assigned a disproportionately high importance when in fact it doesn't do much to separate documents.\r\n\r\nAlternatively, should I be measuring the variance in SHAP values for each feature?",
